h3. Issue Summary

 
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a Kanban Board;
 # Create an Epic;
 # Epic should appear in the Kanban Board;
 # Access Board Settings;
 # Map the Epic status in Backlog and toggle on the Epic Panel;
 # Epic should appear in the Backlog Epic Panel;
 # Remove Backlog by mapping the status in another column;
 # Epic won't show in the board anymore.

h3. Expected Results

When unmapping all statuses from Backlog the Epic Panel should automatically be toggled off, since it's a Backlog only feature.
h3. Actual Results

If all statuses are unmapped from the Backlog before toggling off the Epic Panel, Epics won't be shown in the Kanban Board.
h3. Workaround

Map a status where there are Epics in the Backlog and toggle off the Epic Panel, then map the status again to the right Column.

h3. Steps to reproduce
 # Login to JIRA as an Administrator;
 # Create an Epic in a project;
 # Now create a new issues and choose a different project;
 # Click on the dropdown of the "Epic Link" field;
 # The Epic created before in a different project is listed in this project as well;

h3. What is needed

We want the "Epic Link" field to display only Epics from the selected project.
